Package com.serezk4.command

Class RemoveFirst

java.lang.Object
com.serezk4.command.Command
com.serezk4.command.RemoveFirst
public final class RemoveFirst extends Command
Command to remove the first element from the collection.

The RemoveFirst command removes the first element in the collection managed by CollectionManager. If the collection is empty, an appropriate message is returned.

Since:
1.0

  • Method Details

    • execute

      public Response execute(Request request)
      Executes the command to remove the first element from the collection.

      If the collection is empty, a response indicating this is returned. Otherwise, the first element is removed, and a success message is returned.

      Specified by:
      execute in class Command
      Parameters:
      request - the request to execute (unused for this command)
      Returns:
      a Response indicating whether the first element was removed or the collection was already empty
